===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|Breoton}}, {{m|ang|Bryten}} etc., from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|Britannia}}; later reinforced by {{etyl|xno|en}} {{m|fro|Britaine}}, {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|Bretaigne}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|Brittannia}}, variant of {{m|la|Britannia}}, from {{m|la|Britannī}} (see Etymology 2, below).

====Proper noun====
{{en-proper noun|s}}

# The island of [[Great Britain]], consisting of [[England]], [[Scotland]] and [[Wales]]. {{defdate|from 10th c.}}
# {{label|en|now|historical}} [[Brittany]]. {{defdate|from 13th c.}}
# {{label|en|now|historical}} The British state and its dominions and holdings; the [[British Empire]]. {{defdate|from 17th c.}}
# {{label|en|in the plural}} The [[British Empire]]. {{defdate|from 19th c.}}
